  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I keep Instagram private from Facebook friends and contacts?",
  "response": "To keep your Instagram account private from your Facebook friends and contacts, you can follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Set Your Instagram Account to Private**\n   - Open the Instagram app.\n   - Go to your profile by tapping on your profile picture at the bottom right.\n   - Tap on the three horizontal lines (hamburger menu) at the top right.\n   - Go to **Settings**.\n   - Tap on **Privacy**.\n   - Under the \"Account Privacy\" section, toggle on **Private Account**. This means that only people you approve can see your posts and stories.\n\n### 2. **Remove Facebook Linking**\nIf your Instagram account is linked to your Facebook account, consider unlinking them:\n   - Go to your Instagram profile.\n   - Tap on the three horizontal lines at the top right and select **Settings**.\n   - Tap on **Account**.\n   - Tap on **Linked Accounts** and select **Facebook**.\n   - Unlink your Facebook account.\n\n### 3. **Manage Contacts**\nYou can also prevent your contacts on Facebook from seeing your Instagram account:\n   - In the **Privacy** settings of your Instagram, check the option called **Connections**. Here, you can manage who can find you on Instagram using your phone number or email, preventing contacts from discovering your profile through Facebook.\n\n### 4. **Review Your Followers**\nIf you've already accepted followers, you can remove them:\n   - Go to your profile and tap on your followers.\n   - Find the follower you wish to remove, tap the three dots next to their name, and select **Remove**.\n\n### 5. **Control who can send you Messages**\nTo limit who can message you:\n   - Go to **Settings**.\n   - Tap on **Privacy** and then **Messages**.\n   - Here, you can control who can send you messages and request to follow you.\n\n### 6. **Be Cautious About Sharing**\nIf you post content to Instagram, be mindful of what you share, as even if your account is private, anyone you allow to follow you can take screenshots or share your posts.\n\n### 7. **Check Facebook Sharing Settings**\nMake sure you're not inadvertently sharing your Instagram posts on your Facebook profile. In Instagram, you can disable sharing to Facebook:\n   - In **Settings**, go to **Account** > **Linked Accounts** > **Facebook** and disconnect or adjust settings.\n\nBy following these steps, you can keep your Instagram private from your Facebook friends and contacts more effectively.",
